<chapter id='sitebot'>
<title>Sitebot</title>

<simplesect id='sitebot_prereq'>
<title>Prerequisites</title>
<para>
You need the following to install and use the sitebot for wzdftpd:
</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>wzdftpd correctly installed and configured</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>an eggdrop (see <ulink url="http://www.egghelp.org">slennox's
eggdrop page</ulink> for help)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>The following executables: <ulink
url="http://www.ncftpd.com/ncftp/">ncftpls</ulink>, df (windows: part of
<ulink url="http://www.cygwin.com">cygwin</ulink>), sitewho and siteuptime (in
tools section of wzdftpd)</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>

</simplesect>

<simplesect id='sitebot_install'>
<title>Installation</title>

<para>
Simply copy files wzdftpd.tcl and wzdftpd.help in your eggdrop's scripts
directory.
</para>

</simplesect>


<simplesect id='sitebot_config'>
<title>Configuration</title>

<para>
Edit files wzdftpd.tcl <emphasis>CAREFULLY</emphasis>, each variable or section
is documented. You'll need to set paths of executables according to your
config.
</para>

<para>
NOTE: after each modification of the .tcl file <emphasis>YOU WILL NEED TO
REHASH THE BOT !</emphasis> (and you'd better check this twice if you bugreport
me something !)
</para>

</simplesect>



</chapter>
